&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 Registered Midwife&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title and Grade:&lt;/strong&gt; Midwife at Band 6&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location/Trust:&lt;/strong&gt; East Suffolk &amp; North Essex Foundation Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wards Covered:&lt;/strong&gt; Maternity and Labour Wards&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay Rates: &lt;/strong&gt;Band 6&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registered Band 6 Midwife&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&quot;We are one of the largest organisation in the Eastern region. Our scale provides exciting opportunities for development, innovation, research, education and training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We want the best staff. You want to make a difference.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for an enthusiastic and friendly Midwife to join our highly motivated Midwifery team in either Ipswich or Colchester Maternity services!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You&#39;ll be working with friendly, motivated, supportive teams to provide excellent care to new Mothers, Babies and their families.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have flexible Bank shifts to suit your current lifestyle with a wide range of working patterns available for Registered Midwives at East Suffolk and North Essex Foundation Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please read the attached Job Description &amp; Person Specification for more information on this amazing position!!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registered Midwife:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 - £21.34-£33.46ph&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your hard work and caring skills, we can offer you some fantastic benefits: –&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Competitive Pay Rates -&lt;/strong&gt;work this week, get paid next week!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;First choice of shifts at your Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flexible working to suit your lifestyle&lt;/strong&gt;– Take control of when you want to work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build holiday allowance for every shift you work&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Book and manage your shifts on the go&lt;/strong&gt;– Access shifts anywhere, anytime online or through your smartphone&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support when you need it – 24/7 365 days –&lt;/strong&gt;Call us anytime on 03332 407 552&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stakeholder pension scheme&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills/Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To apply for these posts, you will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have a minimum of 6 months paid experience as a Registered Midwife&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comply with NMC Professional Registration and keep up to date with current practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Completed Preceptorship Programme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be proficient in the delivery of care to patients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Practice as an accountable midwife in an acute and primary care setting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to make appropriate clinical decisions in light of research, evidence, informed choice and individual circumstances.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure accurate records are kept in accordance with CHS policy and NMC guidelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Carry out procedures and techniques in accordance with agreed policies and standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Undertake regular mandatory training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apply&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Register today for various flexible shifts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information on the roles or details on how to join NHS Professionals, simply get in touch by emailingAnnemarie.davies@nhsprofessionals.nhs.uk or please call me on 07468710081&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look forward to hearing from you soon.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who are NHS Professionals?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS Professionals (NHSP), owned by the Department of Health and Social Care (DHSC), works in partnership with hospital trusts to provide a bank of highly skilled temporary workers who want to work flexibly within the NHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working through the NHSP bank means Trusts don’t have to rely on expensive agencies. Right now, we have over 126,000 members registered on our bank from various roles, grades and specialities, saving the NHS over&lt;strong&gt;£70 million&lt;/strong&gt;each year. This money is then reinvested back into the NHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
